| void;\n}\n\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts - COMPLETE)\n\nThe BuildEngine class provides:\n- **Constructor**: Takes SiteConfig, stores plugins and templates in private maps\n- **registerPlugin()**: Adds plugins to the engine\n- **registerTemplate()**: Registers templates by name\n- **resolvePluginOrder()**: Topological sort implementation using depth-first search\n  - Detects circular dependencies and throws \"Circular dependency detected: {name}\"\n  - Detects missing dependencies and throws \"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\"\n  - Returns Plugin[] in execution order\n- **build()**: Main build process\n  - Creates BuildContext with files, output map, assets map, and data store\n  - Resolves plugin execution order\n  - Executes beforeBuild hooks for all plugins in order\n  - Runs transformContent hooks on all files for each plugin (files mutated each iteration)\n  - Renders each file through its template (or outputs raw content if no template found)\n  - Executes afterBuild hooks for all plugins in order\n  - Returns the fully populated BuildContext\n- **getPlugins()**: Returns shallow copy of plugins array\n- **getTemplates()**: Returns shallow copy of templates map\n\nKey implementation detail: transformContent hooks receive the entire file and return a modified file, allowing each hook to transform all files before the next hook runs.\n\n---\n\n### 4. ALL FILES IN src/core/ (COMPLETE)\n\n**src/core/templates.ts**:\n- `createDefaultTemplate()`: Returns Template named \"default\" that renders HTML with DOCTYPE, title, article wrapper, h1 heading, optional time tag, and content div\n- `createListTemplate()`: Returns Template named \"list\" that renders HTML with DOCTYPE, title, and div with class \"list\" containing content\n\n**src/core/index.ts**:\n- Exports: BuildEngine, createDefaultTemplate, createListTemplate\n- Exports types: BuildContext, ContentFile, Plugin, PluginHooks, SiteConfig, Template\n\n---\n\n### 5. ALL TEST FILES (tests/ - COMPLETE)\n\n#### tests/core.test.ts (15 tests - must continue to pass)\nTests for BuildEngine covering:\n- Plugin registration and template registration\n- Default and list template rendering\n- Raw content output when no template found\n- beforeBuild, transformContent, and afterBuild hooks\n- Plugin dependency resolution (topological sort)\n- Circular and missing dependency detection\n- Multiple plugin transformations in order\n- Shared data store in BuildContext\n- File metadata preservation (author, category, date, tags)\n- Empty file list handling\n\n#### tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts (9 tests)\nExpected plugin behavior:\n- Convert basic markdown (`# Hello`, `**bold**`) to HTML\n- Handle footnotes with `[^1]` syntax → `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n- Render footnote section at bottom with `<section class=\"footnotes\">` and `<li id=\"fn-N\">` entries\n- Convert `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip` containers to `<div class=\"admonition admonition-TYPE\">`\n- Preserve existing HTML content\n- Handle empty content gracefully\n\n#### tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts (8 tests)\nExpected plugin behavior:\n- Rewrite relative image URLs: `./image.png` → `/assets/image.png`\n- Rewrite relative link URLs: `./doc.pdf` → `/assets/doc.pdf`\n- Leave absolute URLs unchanged\n- Generate asset manifest in ctx.data under key \"asset-manifest\" with structure: `{ assets: string[] }`\n- Skip files with no asset references\n- Handle multiple assets in one file\n- Accumulate assets across multiple files\n- Don't double-process already-rewritten URLs (starting with `/assets/`)\n\n#### tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts (8 tests)\nExpected plugin behavior:\n- Add \"highlighted\" class to code blocks with language specified\n- Extract language from `class=\"language-javascript\"` and add `data-language=\"javascript\"` to the `<pre>` tag\n- Handle multiple code blocks per file\n- Don't modify code blocks without language specification\n- Don't modify inline `<code>` tags (only `<pre><code>` blocks)\n- Preserve code block content exactly\n\n#### tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts (7 tests)\nExpected plugin behavior:\n- Generate \"search-index.json\" in ctx.output after build\n- Index entries have structure: `{ slug, title, content, tags? }[]`\n- Strip HTML tags from indexed content (extract plain text)\n- Include code block content in searchable text\n- Handle empty file lists\n- Valid JSON output that can be parsed\n- Include tags array if present in file\n\n#### tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts (7 tests)\nExpected plugin behavior:\n- Generate \"sitemap.xml\" in ctx.output\n- Include all `.html` files from ctx.output\n- Include tag pages from taxonomy-tags in ctx.data\n- Include feed.xml URL if present in ctx.output\n- Use baseUrl from config for all URLs\n- Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"... <urlset>...<url><loc>URL</loc>...</url>...</urlset>`\n- Handle sites with no tag pages\n\n#### tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts (7 tests)\nExpected plugin behavior:\n- Store \"dev-server-config\" in ctx.data\n- Config structure: `{ port: number, routes: Array<{path, handler}>, assetPaths: string[], searchIndexPath: string }`\n- Port defaults to 3000\n- Asset routes from asset-pipeline manifest: `assetPaths` and routes with `handler: 'asset'`\n- Search index path: `/search-index.json` (if present in ctx.output)\n- Content routes: one per `.html` file in ctx.output with `handler: 'static'`\n- Gracefully handle missing asset-pipeline data\n\n#### tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts (8 tests)\nExpected plugin behavior:\n- Generate \"feed.xml\" in ctx.output\n- Valid RSS 2.0 XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"... <rss version=\"2.0\"><channel>...<item>...</item>...</channel></rss>`\n- Items have HTML content wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n- Items include tags as `<category>` elements (from taxonomy-tags in ctx.data)\n- Channel title from config.title\n- Items sorted by date newest first (files without dates handled gracefully)\n- Feed and item links use baseUrl from config\n\n#### tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts (9 tests)\nExpected plugin behavior:\n- Build tag map in beforeBuild: `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', Map<string, ContentFile[]>)`\n- Generate tag listing pages in afterBuild: `tags/{tagname}.html`\n- Tag pages list all files with that tag\n- Tag names normalized to lowercase (case-insensitive grouping)\n- Handle files without tags\n- Handle files with multiple tags\n- Handle empty file lists\n\n---\n\n### 6. package.json (COMPLETE)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. tsconfig.json (COMPLETE)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. ADDITIONAL CONFIG FILES\n\n**vitest.config.ts**: